# Naryn, Dzhidinsky District, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Naryn (; , Narin) is a rural locality (a selo) in Dzhidinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 357 as of 2017. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Naryn is located 64&nbsp;km west of Petropavlovka (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kharatsay is the nearest rural locality.
